# Business Context

## Brand & company
- Product: Alpha Medic (AM)
- Publisher: Code 3 Tek LLC (C3T) — Arizona LLC, founder Kyle Winterstein
- Domain: AlphaMedic.app
- Logo: gradient hexagon with ECG trace through capital A

## Product positioning
- Reference tool category (Tarascon / Limmer shelf), NOT enterprise medical software
- Direct competitor: Paramedic Protocol Provider (PPP) — paginated text menus, no visuals, no AI
- Legacy regional incumbent: CAREMSG — paragraph-form text, unsearchable

## Business model
- B2C paramedic-direct: $5.99/month or $49.99/year, 7-day free trial
- Free tier: Universal layer + NASEMSO + limited Scenario AI
- Paid: Tier 1 visual flowcharts + unlimited Scenario AI
- Departments are a Phase 8 upsell, not the foundation
- National scope from launch via region selector. NEVER architect AZ-only assumptions

## Content tiers
1. Universal: drug ref, dose calculator, hospital quick-call, NASEMSO — every user, day one
2. Tier 1: hand-built visual flowcharts (currently Central AZ Red Book 2026)
3. Tier 2: state PDFs in Supabase Storage with full-text search
4. Tier 3: NASEMSO National Model EMS Clinical Guidelines (NMG) — universal fallback

## Legal model
Disclaimers + attribution + version dates + source links. Same posture as Tarascon, Limmer, PPP.
NOT a medical device. NOT pursuing per-agency permissions or formal medical director endorsements.
Reference publisher posture.

## Build discipline
- Build for proven demand. Do NOT refactor Phase 1–7 in anticipation of Phase 8 features.
- Phase 1 priority: finish remaining flowcharts, then PPP gap-closing features
  (Favorites, Hospital Quick-Call tab, Broselow on Calculator)
- App Store + Google Play submission target: Q3 2026